text_cap: Every angler has had this experience
thinking of fishing the last cast and then packing up
but it often ends up with cast after cast
and in the end
more than 20 casts are added
Once I went wild fishing
the sky was getting late
and I told myself it was the last cast
As soon as I cast the line
a fish bit the bait
but I didn't catch it
I thought I would definitely catch one on the next cast
Well, one after another
I just couldn't stop
Newcomers are even more likely to get caught
They are reluctant to leave when there's a fish biting
This is actually the charm of fishing
You never know what the next cast will bring
Fishing is like this
the more you fish
the more addicted you become
We need some self-control
set a reasonable end time for ourselves
and don't be trapped by the 'last cast' curse
otherwise time will slip away quietly
